UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 361
1 A RESOLUTION honoring and expressing support for law enforcement officers in
2 Kentucky and throughout the United States.
3 WHEREAS, more than 800,000 law enforcement officers in the United States risk
4 their lives daily to serve and protect their communities, including more than 7,000
5 officers within the Commonwealth of Kentucky; and
6 WHEREAS, dating back to 1786, there have been more than 24,000 law
7 enforcement officers who have fallen in the line of duty. The names of those heroes are
8 inscribed on the walls of the National Law Enforcement Officers Memorial, and among
9 them are 670 from the Commonwealth of Kentucky; and
10 WHEREAS, this nation's law enforcement officers perform their difficult and
11 dangerous job honorably and professionally, with the overwhelming majority of
12 Americans having responded positively to their interactions with law enforcement
13 officers; and
14 WHEREAS, the innovative and dedicated efforts of law enforcement officers have
15 successfully reduced crime rates over the past three decades from the historic highs
16 experienced in the 1990s; and
17 WHEREAS, the environment for law enforcement officers has become increasingly
18 more hostile, and their safety has become more precarious, with over 79,000 law
19 enforcement officers having been assaulted by criminals in 2023, the highest law
20 enforcement officer assault rate in the past 10 years, and 1,055 officers having been shot
21 during the past three years, with 172 killed in the line of duty; and
22 WHEREAS, more than 2,500 law enforcement officers in the United States have
23 died in the line of duty during the past decade; and
24 WHEREAS, law enforcement officers typically encounter between 400 and 600
25 traumatic events during their careers, compared with three or four for the average citizen;
26 and
27 WHEREAS, the unusually high number of traumatic events experienced by law
Page 1 of 3
