UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 361
1 enforcement officers has contributed to a 54 percent higher suicide rate among law
2 enforcement officers than among other workers in the United States; and
3 WHEREAS, the number of full-time state and local law enforcement officers
4 dropped by 5.3 percent between 2019 and 2021, the equivalent of nearly 37,000 fewer
5 officers, resulting in a dangerously low number of sworn officers to serve and protect
6 communities in the nation; and
7 WHEREAS, supporting law enforcement officers with the equipment, training, and
8 funding needed to protect American communities from criminal violence has long
9 received overwhelming public support from across the political spectrum;
10 NOW, THEREFORE,
11 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the General Assembly of the
12 Commonwealth of Kentucky:
13 Section 1. The House of Representatives expresses its highest respect to law
14 enforcement officers and values their service within the Commonwealth of Kentucky and
15 throughout the United States of America.
16 Section 2. The House of Representatives furthermore expresses its highest
17 honor to those self-sacrificing law enforcement officers who have died or been injured in
18 the line of duty, and concurrently honors the brave families of those officers.
19 Section 3. The House of Representatives urges the federal government and local
20 governments to take further measures to maximize the safety and well-being of law
21 enforcement officers throughout their jurisdictions by recruiting and retaining more law
22 enforcement officers; improving the training and equipping of law enforcement officers;
23 ensuring, when given the jurisdiction, harsh penalties are in place for assaulting or killing
24 law enforcement officers; increasing mental health resources for law enforcement
25 officers; and ensuring that law enforcement officers receive the support and resources
26 they need to keep safe the citizens of not only the Commonwealth, but also the entire
27 United States. Furthermore, the House of Representatives entreats the Senate to join with
Page 2 of 3
